[Reporter Dina] Wedding bells
are ringing today in Hale, Maryland.

01:28:17.995 --> 01:28:22.207
Maggie Carpenter, always a bride,
never a bridesmaid, is attempting...

01:28:22.291 --> 01:28:24.584
to complete
her fourth wedding ceremony.

01:28:24.668 --> 01:28:27.503
We'll be back when results are in.
Back to you, Jessica.

01:28:27.545 --> 01:28:29.713
The turnout for this morning's
ceremony is...

01:28:29.797 --> 01:28:31.924
usually saved
for royalty or movie stars,

01:28:32.007 --> 01:28:34.884
but Maggie Carpenter
is Hale, Maryland's very own star.

01:28:34.968 --> 01:28:37.261
T-shirts here.
I got, "Bye, Bye, Bride-ee."

01:28:37.345 --> 01:28:39.680
I got, "What Part of 'l Do'
Don't You Understand?"

01:28:39.764 --> 01:28:42.391
Get your "Runaway Bride"
T-shirts here.

01:28:42.474 --> 01:28:43.975
Will she or won't she?

01:28:44.017 --> 01:28:46.519
That is on the minds of several
hundred folks standing here,

01:28:46.561 --> 01:28:50.689
not to mention on the mind of groom
number four, who is missing in action.

01:28:50.773 --> 01:28:53.692
- He's gonna stand me up.
- Of course he's gonna come,

01:28:53.775 --> 01:28:57.445
because today I saw
eight geese flying in a "V"

01:28:57.528 --> 01:28:59.572
You with the lucky geese!
You always see geese!

01:28:59.655 --> 01:29:00.823
Not eight!

01:29:00.865 --> 01:29:03.825
- And in a "V"
- Eight is better?

01:29:03.867 --> 01:29:07.704
- Eight in a "V" Can you imagine?
- "V" "V" for, uh--

01:29:07.787 --> 01:29:10.915
- Victory? Victory!
- Great!

01:29:10.998 --> 01:29:13.625
- And... Velcro?
- Okay.

01:29:13.709 --> 01:29:15.544
Velcro! Stick together!

01:29:15.627 --> 01:29:19.547
- Virginal.
- No, no.

01:29:19.630 --> 01:29:22.967
I-I'm sweaty, I'm nervous.
Where are my bags?

01:29:23.133 --> 01:29:25.260
- Okay. No.
- No bags. Bags are for later.

01:29:25.344 --> 01:29:29.138
- Rub your ears.
- Rub your ears. That's a great idea.

01:29:29.222 --> 01:29:33.934
That's a very good idea. Rub your ears.
Cory does that to me sometimes.

01:29:33.976 --> 01:29:37.937
- A little "ooo," and you just "whoo."
- We do it to the dog.

01:29:37.979 --> 01:29:40.314
[Vendor]
Get your "I don't think she will" shirt.

01:29:40.398 --> 01:29:43.150
These shirts are not sold in stores.

01:29:43.234 --> 01:29:45.777
[Excited Chattering]

01:29:45.819 --> 01:29:49.155
- Here comes Ike Graham!
- Show time.

01:29:51.490 --> 01:29:54.993
That's better.
It's pretty nice, actually.

01:29:55.077 --> 01:29:57.454
- Yeah, it's nice.
- He's here!

01:29:57.495 --> 01:30:01.040
[Screams]
Oh, the ear! Ahh! I see him!

01:30:01.124 --> 01:30:03.459
Ike Graham has arrived at church.

01:30:03.501 --> 01:30:05.669
[Excited Chattering]

01:30:05.752 --> 01:30:07.796
- Is this your first marriage?
- Is this your last marriage?

01:30:07.879 --> 01:30:09.881
[Male Reporter]
Any little Grahams in the future?

01:30:09.964 --> 01:30:11.799
[Cory] Oh, he gets whacked!

01:30:11.841 --> 01:30:14.760
- All right, okay.
- This is such a good sign.

01:30:14.843 --> 01:30:16.595
All right! Okay!

01:30:16.678 --> 01:30:18.972
Get this--
Who makes this stuff?

01:30:19.014 --> 01:30:22.850
- The veil is not attacking you.
- Okay, okay.

01:30:22.934 --> 01:30:27.562
- Now is the time to calm down.
- Yes, okay.

01:30:27.646 --> 01:30:31.649
Cause if you don't get calm,
we won't get your dress on.

01:30:31.691 --> 01:30:34.360
A girl can't get married in flannel.

01:30:36.612 --> 01:30:40.740
He's the one.
He really is the one.

01:30:40.824 --> 01:30:43.868
- [Excited Chattering]
- You're not invited.

01:30:43.951 --> 01:30:46.078
Go back to New York.
Get outta here.

01:30:46.161 --> 01:30:48.914
- He's the one!
- [Excited Giggling]

01:30:48.997 --> 01:30:50.332
He's the one!

01:30:50.373 --> 01:30:52.917
We gotta hurry 'cause
the Sunday school kids are coming.

01:30:53.000 --> 01:30:54.960
- Mrs. Pressman.
- There's no microphone.

01:30:55.044 --> 01:30:59.005
- Please, put it there. No, no fun.
- You're no fun.

01:30:59.047 --> 01:31:01.007
I was gonna do
this Scorsese thing--

01:31:01.049 --> 01:31:03.843
- Whatever. Just do it. Shoot, shoot.
- Ike.

01:31:03.885 --> 01:31:07.971
Friends! Oh, God!

01:31:08.055 --> 01:31:10.682
Thank you, thank you,
thank you.

01:31:10.724 --> 01:31:15.227
- Thank you. We are friends, aren't we?
- Of course we are.

01:31:15.311 --> 01:31:18.105
- You'll be my best man.
- Good, but I'm not sure I'm the best.

01:31:18.188 --> 01:31:20.357
Go see the pastor.
He'll tell you what to do.

01:31:20.398 --> 01:31:21.399
All right.

01:31:21.483 --> 01:31:24.152
If someone will tell me
what to do.

01:31:24.235 --> 01:31:26.320
Mmm. You always
looked great in that suit.

01:31:26.403 --> 01:31:28.864
And, Ike?

01:31:28.906 --> 01:31:31.574
I'm happy for you, honey.

01:31:31.658 --> 01:31:35.536
I have a car out back for you
in case she decides to run.

01:31:36.787 --> 01:31:39.623
I have an invitation.
Lou! He's with me.

01:31:44.460 --> 01:31:46.420
You look terrible.

01:31:46.504 --> 01:31:49.590
Thanks.

01:31:49.673 --> 01:31:51.925
Here.

01:31:51.967 --> 01:31:55.386
- Ike, I'm glad it's you.
- Really?

01:31:55.428 --> 01:31:57.430
I wouldn't want to have
found out...

01:31:57.513 --> 01:31:59.932
I wasn't the one
for her in the fourth quarter.

01:32:02.767 --> 01:32:06.020
Well, Coach,
any final advice?

01:32:07.063 --> 01:32:09.565
Maintain eye contact.

01:32:09.606 --> 01:32:13.860
Eye contact.
Eye contact. Eye contact.

01:32:29.581 --> 01:32:31.500
[Whispering]
What have you got going on here?

01:32:31.583 --> 01:32:34.878
You wanna look just special
for the wedding.

01:32:34.961 --> 01:32:38.589
You should thank me and Lou for
lending you the wedding car. '63 Buick.

01:32:38.672 --> 01:32:40.174
Thank you, Mrs. Trout.

01:32:40.257 --> 01:32:42.634
What are you saying?
We're practically family.

01:32:42.718 --> 01:32:46.429
- How's that there?
- My name is Fisher. What's yours?

01:32:46.471 --> 01:32:49.807
Nice. Betty.
That doesn't want to come out, does it?

01:32:49.890 --> 01:32:52.267
- You just pulled a hair from my neck.
- There we are.

01:32:52.309 --> 01:32:55.353
-Mrs. Trout, please. This is my wedding.
-Yes.

01:32:55.437 --> 01:32:57.355
Sit down. Thank you.
We're starting soon.

01:32:57.438 --> 01:33:00.107
- Who was that?
- Mrs. Trout.

01:33:00.149 --> 01:33:02.192
- He doesn't have a--
- Don't do-- Don't.

01:33:02.276 --> 01:33:05.195
I just want that to be able to--
Fold it in the pocket.

01:33:05.278 --> 01:33:09.615
- Right in the pocket.
- Please! Just go-- [Sighs]

01:33:09.657 --> 01:33:13.785
- Good luck, sweet girl.
- Oh, thank you, Grandma. I love you.

01:33:13.827 --> 01:33:17.622
- I'm really rooting for this one.
- Okay, Dad.

01:33:17.664 --> 01:33:20.082
[Cory]
The place is packed...

01:33:20.166 --> 01:33:22.418
with the whole town of Hale
on the bride's side,

01:33:22.501 --> 01:33:26.921
and with many
New Yorkers on the groom's side.

01:33:27.005 --> 01:33:29.966
- Is this taken?
- No.

01:33:30.049 --> 01:33:32.509
I'm Elaine from Manhattan.

01:33:32.551 --> 01:33:35.220
- I'm Bob, Maggie's fourth attempt.
- I'm sorry.

01:33:35.303 --> 01:33:39.056
That's okay.
There's a lid for every pot.

01:33:39.140 --> 01:33:42.518
And I'm comfortable with Ike.

01:33:42.559 --> 01:33:47.313
It's like Jack Dempsey lost
his heavyweight title to a New Yorker.

01:33:47.355 --> 01:33:50.650
Right. Gene Tunney.

01:33:52.026 --> 01:33:53.986
- Whoa.
- Spit!

01:33:55.362 --> 01:33:57.280
Let's go.

01:33:58.740 --> 01:34:02.868
Uh, okay. No sauntering down the aisle.
I don't like that.

01:34:02.952 --> 01:34:05.912
- Make time. Just get there. Just go.
- Fine.

01:34:05.996 --> 01:34:08.289
% [Organ]

01:34:19.215 --> 01:34:21.217
All rise, please.

01:34:26.555 --> 01:34:29.390
% ["The Wedding March"]

01:34:38.189 --> 01:34:40.233
The bride is walking
down the aisle.

01:34:40.316 --> 01:34:43.736
Maggie Carpenter
is walking down the aisle.

01:34:43.819 --> 01:34:46.780
[Crowd Gasping]

01:34:48.406 --> 01:34:52.201
- Oh, she's pausing.
- Stay with me.

01:34:52.243 --> 01:34:54.203
[Bob]
Keep eye contact.

01:34:54.245 --> 01:34:56.413
[Relieved Chuckling]

01:35:05.296 --> 01:35:08.090
[Pastor]
Please be seated. Thank you.

01:35:08.173 --> 01:35:10.508
I sneaked in a camera.

01:35:10.592 --> 01:35:13.427
We are gathered here today--

01:35:13.511 --> 01:35:14.762
Please, no cameras.

01:35:14.845 --> 01:35:18.890
Could we hold off photos
until the end of the ceremony?

01:35:18.932 --> 01:35:20.350
Thank you.

01:35:21.601 --> 01:35:23.644
No.

01:35:23.728 --> 01:35:27.272
- [Pastor] Where's she going?
- [Ike] Don't.

01:35:27.356 --> 01:35:31.276
- Maggie!
- Block the doors!

01:35:32.735 --> 01:35:35.362
No, Maggie, don't!

01:35:41.701 --> 01:35:44.245
Oh, never a dull moment
at a Maggie wedding.

01:35:44.287 --> 01:35:46.372
There's a man coming with
lots of candy in his pocket.

01:35:46.455 --> 01:35:49.333
If you tickle him, he'll give you all
his candy. Here you go, little queen.

01:35:49.416 --> 01:35:51.918
- Maggie!
-Just tickle him.

01:35:53.628 --> 01:35:57.298
- [Children] Give us some candy!
- Whoa. No, not me.

01:35:57.381 --> 01:36:00.258
Get the naughty bride.
Naughty bride.

01:36:00.300 --> 01:36:03.594
No, no.
It's an Armani suit.

01:36:05.805 --> 01:36:08.223
Wait!

01:36:10.058 --> 01:36:11.851
- Wait!
- Maggie!

01:36:13.061 --> 01:36:15.438
Go. Go. Go, go.

01:36:16.814 --> 01:36:20.442
Maggie! Maggie!

01:36:20.484 --> 01:36:23.820
Don't do it! Don't!

01:36:23.903 --> 01:36:25.821
Maggie!

01:36:25.905 --> 01:36:29.116
- He's running after her.
- He's in pretty good shape too.

01:36:29.158 --> 01:36:32.744
Maggie! No, Maggie!

01:36:32.827 --> 01:36:34.746
Where do you think she's going?

01:36:34.829 --> 01:36:37.164
Wherever it is,
she'll be there by 1 0:30 tomorrow.

01:36:39.416 --> 01:36:41.626
Maggie! No!

01:36:47.006 --> 01:36:48.966
Maggie!

01:36:49.008 --> 01:36:51.968
No! No!

01:36:52.010 --> 01:36:54.554
Maggie!

01:37:00.184 --> 01:37:02.352
Mr. Graham! Mr. Graham!

01:37:05.188 --> 01:37:08.941
[Mooing]

01:37:09.024 --> 01:37:11.652
- Mr. Graham, what is your next move?
- How do you feel now?

01:37:11.693 --> 01:37:13.987
- What will you do?
- I know you must feel terrible.

01:37:14.029 --> 01:37:16.114
[Chattering Continues]

01:37:16.197 --> 01:37:19.492
- Mr. Graham, talk to us.
- That's enough.

01:37:19.533 --> 01:37:21.535
Come on. Leave him alone.

01:37:29.208 --> 01:37:31.627
"Hardware Honey
Goes Nuts and Bolts."

01:37:31.710 --> 01:37:33.628
How many times
is she gonna do this?

01:37:38.049 --> 01:37:41.927
% Aura Lee %

01:37:42.010 --> 01:37:45.430
- % Aura Lee %
- [Cory] Finally, in local news,

01:37:45.513 --> 01:37:48.641
the mayor has requested that we all
stop gossiping about last week's...

01:37:48.724 --> 01:37:51.560
Maggie Carpenter "almost wedding."

01:37:51.602 --> 01:37:54.688
This is Cory Flemming
for W-HALE saying...

01:37:54.771 --> 01:37:57.565
may the good Lord make you smart
enough to live in a small town.

01:37:57.649 --> 01:37:59.609
And we cut.

01:37:59.692 --> 01:38:02.528
[Lee]
Camera loves ya.

01:38:04.404 --> 01:38:07.240
- Hey, you okay?
- Yeah.

01:38:07.323 --> 01:38:09.742
I'm closing.
You wanna go to Butch's for a drink?

01:38:09.825 --> 01:38:12.786
Uh, you know,
I'm gonna finish up here,

01:38:12.870 --> 01:38:14.913
and then I think
I'll just head home.

01:38:14.996 --> 01:38:16.998
Okay.

01:38:18.791 --> 01:38:21.460
You know,

01:38:21.544 --> 01:38:24.296
I was thinking about
that "V" thing.

01:38:24.379 --> 01:38:27.340
And I think
the "V" in the geese...

01:38:27.424 --> 01:38:32.094
was half of a "W" for--

01:38:32.178 --> 01:38:34.096
For, uh--

01:38:34.179 --> 01:38:38.308
- W-W-What are you talking about?
- Wedding! Wedding.

01:38:38.349 --> 01:38:42.103
You just gotta get
the rest of your ducks in a row.

01:38:43.854 --> 01:38:46.356
Thank you.

01:38:49.692 --> 01:38:51.819
- So you still think that he--
- You're quick.

01:38:51.902 --> 01:38:54.613
You're very quick.

01:38:59.659 --> 01:39:02.661
[Sighs]

01:39:13.462 --> 01:39:16.298
[Male Singer]
% I thought that %

01:39:16.381 --> 01:39:21.010
% You'd be loving me %

01:39:21.094 --> 01:39:26.807
% I thought you were the one
who'd stay forever %

01:39:28.350 --> 01:39:33.646
% But now forever's
come and gone %

01:39:33.729 --> 01:39:39.317
%And I'm still here alone %

01:39:40.568 --> 01:39:44.196
% 'Cause you were only playin' %

01:39:44.280 --> 01:39:47.491
% You were only playin'
with my heart %

01:39:47.574 --> 01:39:51.244
% I was never waiting %

01:39:51.327 --> 01:39:55.498
% I was never waiting
for the tears to start %

01:39:55.581 --> 01:39:59.709
% It was you %

01:39:59.751 --> 01:40:03.212
% Who put the clouds around me %

01:40:03.296 --> 01:40:06.757
% It was you %

01:40:06.840 --> 01:40:10.343
% Who made the tears fall down %

01:40:10.427 --> 01:40:13.846
% It was you %

01:40:13.930 --> 01:40:17.349
% Who broke my heart in pieces %

01:40:17.433 --> 01:40:21.186
% It was you, it was you %

01:40:21.269 --> 01:40:26.232
% Who made my blue eyes blue
Ooh, ooh %

01:40:26.315 --> 01:40:29.026
% I never should've trusted you %

01:40:29.109 --> 01:40:31.778
Okay, here we go.

01:40:31.861 --> 01:40:35.948
% I thought that I'd be %

01:40:36.032 --> 01:40:38.992
% All you need %

01:40:39.076 --> 01:40:42.954
% In your eyes I thought
I saw my--%

01:40:43.037 --> 01:40:45.873
- Ike, how's it goin'?
- Hey, Marvin.

01:40:45.957 --> 01:40:47.875
That good, huh?

01:40:47.958 --> 01:40:51.795
% 'Cause you had me
believin' in a lie %

01:40:51.878 --> 01:40:54.756
% Guess I couldn't see it %

01:40:54.797 --> 01:40:59.843
% I guess I couldn't see it
till I saw the light %

01:40:59.927 --> 01:41:03.096
% It was you %

01:41:03.138 --> 01:41:06.849
% It was you %

01:41:06.932 --> 01:41:10.394
% Who put those clouds around me %

01:41:10.477 --> 01:41:13.813
% It was you %

01:41:13.897 --> 01:41:17.483
% Who made the tears fall down %

01:41:17.566 --> 01:41:20.569
% Only you %

01:41:20.652 --> 01:41:24.531
- [Phone Ringing]
-% Who broke my heart in pieces %

01:41:24.614 --> 01:41:27.283
[Answering Machine]
Hi, it's me.

01:41:27.325 --> 01:41:31.286
Leave a message after the beep.
[Machine Beeps]

01:41:31.328 --> 01:41:33.580
[Dial Tone]

01:41:37.333 --> 01:41:39.168
Hello, Ike.

01:41:49.718 --> 01:41:54.097
Don't tell me my doorman
is one of your many admirers?

01:41:56.099 --> 01:41:58.684
I'm making friends with your cat.

01:42:00.019 --> 01:42:01.937
Is it okay that I'm here?

01:42:02.020 --> 01:42:05.815
I don't have much choice
in the matter, do l?

01:42:05.857 --> 01:42:08.985
But, I can't speak for Italics.
Traitor.

01:42:09.068 --> 01:42:11.111
[Purring]

01:42:11.195 --> 01:42:12.988
I don't blame you for being mad.

01:42:13.030 --> 01:42:15.782
Or furious.

01:42:16.866 --> 01:42:19.702
Irate? Livid.

01:42:19.785 --> 01:42:22.538
- [Meowing]
- What is it, Maggie?

01:42:22.621 --> 01:42:24.539
You here on business?

01:42:24.623 --> 01:42:27.959
By the way, I saw your lamps.

01:42:28.042 --> 01:42:32.129
They're terrific. Yeah, really.

01:42:32.212 --> 01:42:35.465
- It's something I've always wanted to--
- [Door Closes]

01:42:35.549 --> 01:42:38.926
You could make breaking and entering
into a new career.

01:42:42.137 --> 01:42:44.848
So, what are you
doing here anyway?

01:42:47.725 --> 01:42:51.270
I wanted to talk to you...

01:42:51.353 --> 01:42:56.524
about why I run,

01:42:56.608 --> 01:42:59.861
sometimes ride, away from things.

01:43:02.655 --> 01:43:05.324
- Does it matter?
- I think so.

01:43:05.407 --> 01:43:07.325
[Clears Throat]

01:43:07.409 --> 01:43:12.580
When I was walking down the aisle,
I was walking toward somebody...

01:43:12.663 --> 01:43:18.376
who had no idea who I really was.

01:43:18.460 --> 01:43:23.297
And it was only half
the other person's fault...

01:43:23.380 --> 01:43:28.134
because I had done everything
to convince him...

01:43:28.218 --> 01:43:30.303
that I was exactly what he wanted.

01:43:30.386 --> 01:43:33.847
So, it was good...

01:43:33.931 --> 01:43:38.727
that I didn't go through with it
because it would've been a lie.

01:43:38.810 --> 01:43:42.521
But you--

01:43:42.605 --> 01:43:45.065
You knew the real me.

01:43:47.109 --> 01:43:49.027
Yes, I did.

01:43:49.110 --> 01:43:51.612
I didn't.

01:43:52.989 --> 01:43:57.242
Still, I ended up
chasing a truck.

01:44:10.962 --> 01:44:14.882
I can't, um,
do anything about the truck.

01:44:16.842 --> 01:44:18.760
But, uh--

01:44:23.222 --> 01:44:25.933
- Benedict.
- Arnold.

01:44:26.016 --> 01:44:28.602
I love eggs Benedict.

01:44:28.685 --> 01:44:31.437
I hate all the other
kinds of eggs.

01:44:31.479 --> 01:44:35.691
I hate big weddings,
everybody staring.

01:44:35.774 --> 01:44:38.777
I'd like to get married on
a weekday while everybody's at work.

01:44:38.860 --> 01:44:42.447
And if I ride off into the sunset,
I want my own horse.

01:44:42.530 --> 01:44:44.991
- Should I be writing this down?
- And there's something else.

01:44:45.074 --> 01:44:47.576
No, you can tell me.
Don't--

01:44:47.659 --> 01:44:49.578
Okay.

01:44:54.582 --> 01:44:56.542
These are for you.

01:45:01.921 --> 01:45:04.924
- Used--
- Well, they're mine.

01:45:05.007 --> 01:45:09.970
I'm turning in
my running shoes to you.

01:45:13.223 --> 01:45:15.141
This is serious.

01:45:15.224 --> 01:45:16.892
And there's one more thing.

01:45:16.976 --> 01:45:19.853
I know, the mind reels that
there could be more after this.

01:45:19.937 --> 01:45:23.940
-But, um, if you could just have a seat.
-[Clears Throat]

01:45:27.276 --> 01:45:30.612
Let's just not have that there.

01:45:30.696 --> 01:45:33.406
Okay. Okay.

01:45:38.410 --> 01:45:42.205
- Oh, no. My, God, no.
- No, no. Don't hide your face.

01:45:42.289 --> 01:45:45.291
This happens once in a lifetime,
and it's definitely a first for me.

01:45:45.375 --> 01:45:48.460
You're not gonna want to miss it,
so pay close attention.

01:45:55.216 --> 01:45:59.803
I love you,
Homer Eisenhower Graham.

01:46:02.472 --> 01:46:03.765
Will you marry me?

01:46:03.765 --> 01:46:05.433
Will you marry me?

01:46:11.813 --> 01:46:13.732
[Laughs]

01:46:15.275 --> 01:46:18.486
I gotta think about this
a little bit.

01:46:18.569 --> 01:46:22.656
- Good. I was hoping you would say that.
- You were not! Not true.

01:46:22.739 --> 01:46:25.658
If you'd said yes, I wouldn't
be able to do this next part...

01:46:25.742 --> 01:46:27.577
and I've been practicing so let me--

01:46:29.120 --> 01:46:31.622
Okay.
[Exhales]

01:46:31.705 --> 01:46:34.416
- Ready?
- I'm listening.

01:46:37.960 --> 01:46:39.920
[Sighs]

01:46:42.256 --> 01:46:47.051
I guarantee
that we'll have tough times.

01:46:47.093 --> 01:46:50.221
And I guarantee
that at some point...

01:46:50.304 --> 01:46:53.765
one or both of us
will want to get out.

01:46:55.183 --> 01:46:58.019
But I also guarantee...

01:46:58.102 --> 01:47:01.564
that if I don't ask you to be mine,

01:47:01.647 --> 01:47:04.232
I'll regret it
for the rest of my life.

01:47:05.483 --> 01:47:07.944
'Cause I know in my heart...

01:47:07.986 --> 01:47:11.280
you're the only one for me.

01:47:18.328 --> 01:47:20.955
That's a pretty
good speech, Maggie.

01:47:21.038 --> 01:47:24.499
I borrowed it from
this writer I know.

01:47:26.876 --> 01:47:29.545
So?

01:47:42.598 --> 01:47:46.935
%[Miles Davis]

01:47:55.651 --> 01:47:58.111
Dance with me.

01:48:21.255 --> 01:48:24.466
[Pastor] We are gathered here
today to celebrate the union...

01:48:24.508 --> 01:48:27.844
of Maggie Carpenter and Ike Graham.

01:48:40.188 --> 01:48:43.024
- Do you have the rings?
- Yes.

01:48:43.065 --> 01:48:46.276
Do you, Ike, take Maggie
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

01:48:49.821 --> 01:48:51.739
I do.

01:48:51.823 --> 01:48:56.201
Do you, Maggie, take Ike
to be your lawfully wedded husband?

01:48:56.243 --> 01:48:58.203
I do.

01:48:58.245 --> 01:49:00.997
[Pastor]
In this life that you share together,

01:49:01.039 --> 01:49:05.000
may your individuality
strengthen your love.

01:49:05.084 --> 01:49:08.253
With the power vested in me,

01:49:08.337 --> 01:49:13.049
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

01:49:13.091 --> 01:49:15.968
You may kiss the bride.

01:49:29.187 --> 01:49:30.730
[Applauding]

01:49:45.826 --> 01:49:48.412
Guess what. She did it!

01:49:48.495 --> 01:49:50.747
Maggie Carpenter got married.

01:49:50.831 --> 01:49:53.083
% Alleluia %

01:49:58.045 --> 01:50:00.922
Betty, she did it. She did it!

